  "prompt": "Can an Uber rider select a different Uber driver?",
  "response": "No, an Uber rider cannot directly select a specific Uber driver. When you request a ride through the Uber app, the system automatically matches you with the nearest available driver based on factors like proximity, vehicle type, and driver rating. However, there are a few things riders can do to influence their experience:\n\n1. **Uber Comfort or Premium Options**: Some Uber services, like Uber Comfort or Uber Black, allow you to choose a higher-rated driver or a more luxurious vehicle.\n\n2. **Canceling and Rebooking**: If you\u2019re matched with a driver you\u2019d prefer not to ride with, you can cancel the request (though this may result in a cancellation fee) and request a new ride, which could match you with a different driver.\n\n3. **Ratings and Feedback**: You can rate drivers after your trip, which helps Uber\u2019s algorithm determine future matches.\n\nKeep in mind that repeatedly canceling rides to avoid certain drivers may lead to restrictions on your account, so it\u2019s best to use this option sparingly.",
